title: Serialize/FunctionDefinition-normalized-whitespace
description: A whitespace pragma inside a procedure body survives AST-only serialization, with and without trailing blank lines
tags: $:/tags/wikitext-serialize-normalize-spec
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki-multiple

title: info

The input survives unchanged: this pair is an identity pin, not a
normalization.

Why: a `\whitespace` pragma inside a procedure body is part of the
definition text, which the AST stores verbatim, so even tree-only
serialization keeps it byte-exact, with and without trailing blank lines.

* Covers: $:/plugins/tiddlywiki/wikitext-serialize/rules/fnprocdef.js.
* Mode: ast-only (the Input field withholds the source from the serializer).
+
title: Input
mode: ast-only

\procedure compact()
\whitespace trim
nothing
\end

\procedure trailing()
\whitespace trim

nothing


\end

<<compact>>
